^["stream"]{
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] observe - The current site already has semantic tagging, frame activation, and lightweight eventing, but it still treats hover and page-local modules as stronger organizing surfaces than mobile-first regions and shared runtime state.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] observe - `site.js` owns global frame/mode activation and the spirit easter egg, while `frame-navigator.js` separately owns `g`, `[ ]`, `/`, and `Escape`; this is enough machinery to prove the next gap is arbitration and shared runtime, not lack of metaphoric vocabulary.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] observe - `spw-component-semantics.js` already derives kind, form, role, liminality, and selection, which makes it the natural bridge from authored semantics into portable runtime intent.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] observe - CSS is already rich in hover states and floating surfaces, but the governing model is not yet explicitly mobile-first; region ownership and coarse-pointer behavior remain implicit.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] decide - Plan around four foundations: named page regions, portable inspect/invoke semantics, shared inspectable registers, and block/script host contracts.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:09] taste - Keep magic summonable and inspectable; the calm default should survive even as the runtime surface deepens.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:12] decide - Wrote a distilled semantics note so future implementation can test counterexamples instead of letting metaphor drift across modules.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:12] verify - `poll-review.sh --scope=changed` passed cleanly for the new plan surfaces and `.spw` artifacts.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:20] decide - The user is not attached to current keybindings, which means the runtime can center semantic symmetry rather than preserving arbitrary legacy keys.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:20] revise - The plan now treats prefix/postfix symmetry, brace pivots, and structural wonder as first-class UX constraints instead of secondary aesthetic concerns.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:20] taste - Wonder should arrive as a pivot into clearer structure while preserving orientation, not as decorative motion layered onto already-legible surfaces.
 >>[2026-04-09 20:20] rebase - Refreshed `base_ref` to the current `main` commit after the plan artifact landed so the maintenance surface matches the active lineage.
}

^["open"]{
 ?[regions]: "Which page regions should be universal across routes versus optional per-surface?"
 ?[intent]: "What is the smallest portable interaction vocabulary that cleanly spans touch, pointer, and keyboard?"
 ?[registers]: "Which runtime registers must be first-class before navigator and console can become honest projections?"
 ?[blocks]: "What host contract should exist before Spw blocks and scripts are allowed to shape UI?"
 ?[symmetry]: "What is the canonical normalization from prefix and postfix interaction paths into one semantic register trace?"
 ?[pivots]: "Which structure changes count as local pivots rather than route changes or overlays?"
 ?[wonder]: "Which moments of structural revelation are strong enough to feel magical without violating calm defaults?"
 ?[authoring]: "What is the smallest authoring contract that lets a page become Spw-backed without requiring a full in-browser parser?"
}

^["commits"]{
